  "summary": "OTP email helper silently relays caller data through author's Gmail account",
  "details": "utils/send_email_otp.py exposes otpEmailService(to_email, email_body) which hardcodes the SMTP sender as magizhchisk@gmail.com with an embedded Gmail App Password (avqkjxqzjsrnqims) and connects to smtp.gmail.com:587. Every call to this advertised API authenticates as the author's personal Gmail account and transmits the caller-supplied recipient address and OTP message body through that mailbox. Any installer using the package's public OTP function silently leaks recipient identities and OTP contents to an account they do not control. Additionally, the live Gmail App Password is shipped in importable code, allowing any installer to authenticate as the author and send mail from that account.",
